result.execSummary:
The defendant Wyatt R Walters was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. On one or more other charges, Wyatt R Walters was found not guilty. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Wyatt R Walters is presumed innocent of the not guilty charges.

  • Wyatt R Walters was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Wyatt R Walters was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
